{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ad8630c8-033e-41ea-ae60-488ac5c98ae7","content":"`SafeAreaEdges` isn't a .NET MAUI property — that's likely why it has no effect. Here's what you actually need:\n\n### iOS\nAdd the platform-specific `UseSafeArea` property to your `ContentPage`:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n    <Image Source=\"photo.jpg\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n### Android\nEdge-to-edge requires platform configuration. In your `MainActivity.cs` or `MauiProgram.cs`, ensure the window draws behind system bars:\n\n```csharp\n// In Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs\nprotected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)\n{\n    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n    \n    if (Window != null)\n    {\n        Window.SetStatusBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent);\n        Window.SetNavigationBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent);\n    }\n\n    AndroidX.Core.View.WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false);\n}\n```\n\n> **Note:** On Android 15+ (API 35), edge-to-edge is enforced by default, so this step is mainly needed for older API levels.\n\n### Key points\n- **`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"`** — the actual iOS property to extend behind safe areas\n- **`SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(window, false)`** — tells Android not to inset content for system bars\n- **`Aspect=\"AspectFill\"`** on the Image — ensures it fills the available space without letterboxing","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d32c64be-f6ed-4996-85bc-a1082b07afd2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about making content go edge-to-edge in a .NET MAUI app, going behind the status bar and navigation bar. They've tried `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on the ContentPage but still see padding.\n\nThis is a common .NET MAUI question. Let me think about what's needed:\n\nIn .NET MAUI, to achieve true edge-to-edge content that goes behind system bars, you need to:\n\n1. Set `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on the view (like the `Image`) itself, not just on the page.\n2. On Android, you may also need to opt into edge-to-edge display mode.\n\n\n3. On iOS specifically, you'd use the platform-specific `UseSafeArea=\"False\"` property to disable safe area insets, while Android requires setting up edge-to-edge rendering starting from Android 15 or using platform-specific configurations. `IgnoreSafeArea` is actually a property on `View` in MAUI that controls whether a view respects safe area insets, so that's the right approach for making content go edge-to-edge on both platforms. The user mentioned `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` which isn't a standard MAUI property, so they're likely looking for the actual approach: `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"` on iOS and platform-specific edge-to-edge configuration on Android, combined with setting the image to `AspectFill` to fill the page properly.","outputTokens":1501,"requestId":"D462:2586A7:1C8C327:200E694:6A07BF86"},"id":"2daf0538-6465-4867-b4ab-1d5aeae8c9d8","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:51:56.111Z","parentId":"2ec89985-0152-43e4-9631-2ae0ab6984ee"}
